  "label": "Vespera Tertius Ashmantle Range",
  "description": "Vespera Tertius Ashmantle Range is a basaltic mountain spine rising from ash-choked basins into the planet’s bruise-lit auroral haze. Its slopes are glazed with vitrified cinder and impact glass, forming jagged ribs that shed black scree into wind-carved gullies. Electrostatic storms rake the ridgelines with violet lightning, leaving fulgurite seams and a persistent metallic tang in the air. Vox and auspex returns fracture against the range’s mineral density and constant atmospheric interference, rendering distant landmarks indistinct and unreliable.",
